OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FSeven-week gap advised for 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Felective surgery after     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5FOmicron                    
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Despite a backlog of routine           
OL,6, operations, NHS hospitals are being    
OL,7, advised to delay elective surgical     
OL,8, procedures by at least seven weeks if a
OL,9, patient has just had Omicron.          
OL,11,FUK experts say it is a precaution since
OL,12,Fthe first couple of months following   
OL,13,Finfection is a riskier period, linked  
OL,14,Fto poorer post-operative recovery.     
OL,16,FIn some circumstances the surgery may  
OL,17,Fbe urgent enough to go ahead, however. 
OL,19,FPatients should ideally have had all of
OL,20,Ftheir Covid vaccines too.              
